{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Tomato Sauce","content":["Place ginger, chilli, lemon and salt in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add tomatoes and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a serving bowl and set aside."]},{"title":"Crab Filling","content":["Place coriander, lemon zest, garlic clove, salt, red chilli, and ground cumin in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b> ","Add crabmeat and stir <b>10 sec\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a bowl.","Take one filo pastry sheet, and spoon one eighth of crab filling approximately 5 cm from the edge of one of the short ends. Tuck both sides in and roll up the brik in a neat rectangle shape. Set aside on a plate and fill the rest of the filo sheets in the same way.","Heat oil to a depth of 2 cm in a suitable frying pan. Test the temperature by dropping a small piece of filo pastry into the oil - if it sizzles, the oil is ready.","Fry briks over medium heat in oil for 8 minutes, turning once. When they are golden brown on both sides, drain on paper towels. Serve briks hot, with tomato sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Tomato Sauce","content":["2 cm fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","1 red chilli, halved and deseeded","10 g freshly squeezed lemon juice","1 tsp salt","2 tomatoes, quartered"]},{"title":"Crab Filling","content":["20 g fresh coriander","1 slice lemon zest","1 garlic clove","1 tsp fine sea salt","1 red chilli, halved and deseeded","1 pinch ground cumin","300 g fresh crab meat","8 sheets filo pastry (approx. 48 cm x 25 cm)","oil, for frying"]}],"id":"r170302","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-1gIaNeNYD3A\/XZVQsqQo_mI\/AAAAAAAAdEc\/gAQkHgTzVmg5GeTQ1ErNjQ-RP1PxIUV7gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_V-yS2K-PeaI7DxSc.png","title":"Crab Briks","publishedAt":"2017-05-29T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"61 g","fat":"61 g","uom":"per 8 portions","carbohydrates":"106 g","calories":"5101 kJ \/ 1217 kcal"},"usefulItems":"frying pan, paper towel, hob","hintsAndTricks":["To make 16 smaller crab briks, use half a sheet of filo pastry per portion, and half the amount of crab filling.","Filo pastry dries out very quickly, so handle it carefully. Unroll the sheets of filo pastry, and keep the unused sheets covered with cling film. Remove one at a time, replacing the cling film after each one."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","35m","8 portions"]}